          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>14007</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2009-11-09 15:18:47 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The same problem also occurs when using Selenium&#39;s native &quot;dragAndDropToObject&quot; command. It seems that IE7 somehow can&#39;t cope with a synthetic &quot;mousedown&quot; event triggered on the &quot;dragHandle&quot; element. 
I&#39;m unwilling to invest any more time in trying to find a workaround since this seems like it only affects a limited number of use cases. Closing this as &quot;wontfix&quot; for the moment, will reopen if this issue pops up again in a different context.</thetext>
